def large_legend():
    data = [.4, .4, .4, .4, .4]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(3, 3))
    ax.barh(range(len(data)), data, color=colorlist)
    for i, v in enumerate(labels):
        ax.text(.1, i - .1, str(labels[i]), color='white', fontweight='bold', size=12, 
                path_effects=[PathEffects.Stroke(linewidth=1, foreground='black'),PathEffects.Normal()])
    plt.ylabel(labels)
    plt.gca().set_axis_off()
    plt.show()

def seqIplot(axn, df, chartnum):
    rows = len(df)
    cols = 6
    Z = df.iloc[:,1:len(df.columns)]
    x = np.arange(7)
    y = np.arange(len(df) + 1)
    cmap = colors.ListedColormap(colorlist)
    axn.pcolormesh(x, y, Z, shading='flat', vmin=0, vmax=4, cmap=cmap)
    axn.set_xticklabels(df.columns[1:7])
    axn.set_yticklabels([])
    axn.tick_params(axis=u'y', which=u'both',length=0)
    axn.set(ylabel="n=" + str(len(df)) + '\n' + str(round((len(df) / len(ltdb_series)) * 100)) + '%'  )
    axn.set_title('cluster ' + str(chartnum))

struggling_clusters=[]
def seqrplot(axn, df, chartnum):
    seqcount=pd.DataFrame(df.groupby(df.columns[1:7].tolist(),as_index=False).size())
    seqcount.reset_index(inplace=True)
    seqcount=seqcount.rename({0:'reccount'}, axis=1)
    Z=np.array([])
    while (Z.shape[0] / len(df)) < 0.25:
        mostfreq=seqcount.reccount.idxmax()
        mostfreqcount=seqcount.reccount.max()
        if Z.shape[0]==0:
            Z=np.repeat(np.array(seqcount.loc[[mostfreq], ['1970', '1980', '1990', '2000', '2010', '2019']]), mostfreqcount, axis=0)
        else:
            Z=np.concatenate((Z, np.repeat(np.array(seqcount.loc[[mostfreq], ['1970', '1980', '1990', '2000', '2010', '2019']]), mostfreqcount, axis=0)))
        seqcount.drop(mostfreq, inplace=True)
    if sum(Z[:,-1]==colorcode.loc[colorcode['labels']=='Struggling', 'numcode'].values[0]) / Z.shape[0] >= 0.5:
        struggling_clusters.append(chartnum - 1)

    rows = Z.shape[0]
    cols = 6
    x = np.arange(7)
    y = np.arange(rows + 1)
    cmap = colors.ListedColormap(colorlist)
    axn.pcolormesh(x, y, Z, shading='flat', vmin=0, vmax=4, cmap=cmap)
    axn.set_xticklabels(df.columns[1:7])
    axn.set_yticklabels([])
    axn.tick_params(axis=u'y', which=u'both',length=0)
    axn.set(ylabel="n=" + str(Z.shape[0]))
    axn.set_title('Most Frequent Patterns: Cluster ' + str(chartnum) + ', Density Coverage=' + str(round((Z.shape[0] / len(df))*100,ndigits=1)) + '%')

Using Jaccard to compare R with Ward and Max distance¶

In [18]:
# copied from https://stackoverflow.com/questions/56217197/how-to-calculate-jaccard-similarity-distance-between-two-list-of-strings
def jaccard_similarity(list1, list2):
    intersection = len(set(list1).intersection(list2)) #no need to call list here
    union = len(list1 + list2) - intersection #you only need to call len once here
    return intersection / union #also no need to cast to float as this will be done for you
In [19]:
jaccard_r_p=[]
jaccard_r_pm=[]
rlist_all=[]
plist_all=[]
pmlist_all=[]
for r,p,pm, descript in zip(cluster_type['Rnum'],cluster_type['Pnum'],cluster_type['PMnum'], cluster_type['ClustDescript']):
    rlist=list(ltdb_seq_cluster[ltdb_seq_cluster['Rseqclust']==r]['CensusTract'])
    plist=list(ltdb_seq_cluster[ltdb_seq_cluster['Pseqclust']==p-1]['CensusTract']) 
    pmlist=list(ltdb_seq_cluster[ltdb_seq_cluster['PMseqclust']==pm-1]['CensusTract']) 
    rlist_all.extend(list(ltdb_seq_cluster[ltdb_seq_cluster['Rseqclust']==r]['CensusTract'] + descript))
    plist_all.extend(list(ltdb_seq_cluster[ltdb_seq_cluster['Pseqclust']==p-1]['CensusTract'] + descript)) 
    pmlist_all.extend(list(ltdb_seq_cluster[ltdb_seq_cluster['PMseqclust']==pm-1]['CensusTract'] + descript))
    if not math.isnan(r) and not math.isnan(p):
        jaccard_r_p.append(round(jaccard_similarity(rlist, plist),3))
    else:
        jaccard_r_p.append(None)
    if not math.isnan(r) and not math.isnan(pm):
        jaccard_r_pm.append(round(jaccard_similarity(rlist, pmlist),3))
    else:
        jaccard_r_pm.append(None)
cluster_type['J_Ward']=pd.Series(jaccard_r_p)
cluster_type['J_Max']=pd.Series(jaccard_r_pm)

colordict={'Stable Struggling': 'cyan', 'Stable Blue Collar': 'violet', 'Blue Collar to Struggling': 'orange', 'Alternate Blue Collar, Young Urban': 'orange'}
def overlay_map_legend(seqclust, clusterlist):
    plt.ioff()
    if seqclust=='Pseqclust':
        labels=[cluster_type[cluster_type['Pnum']==x+1]['ClustDescript'].values[0] for x in clusterlist]
    elif seqclust=='PMseqclust':
        labels=[cluster_type[cluster_type['PMnum']==x+1]['ClustDescript'].values[0] for x in clusterlist]
    else:
        labels=[cluster_type[cluster_type['Rnum']==x]['ClustDescript'].values[0] for x in clusterlist]

    maxletters=len(max(labels, key=len))
    colorlist=[colordict[x] for x in labels]
    bars = [.3] * len(clusterlist)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(maxletters/6.6, len(clusterlist) - len(clusterlist)/3 ))  # trial and error sizing
    ax.barh(range(len(bars)), bars, color=colorlist)
    for i, v in enumerate(labels):
        ax.text(.01, i - .1, str(labels[i]), color='white', fontweight='bold', size=13, 
                path_effects=[PathEffects.Stroke(linewidth=1, foreground='black'),PathEffects.Normal()])
    plt.ylabel(labels)
    plt.gca().set_axis_off()

    fig1 = plt.gcf()
    #maplegend=os.path.join(htmldir, 'maplegend.png')
    fig1.savefig('maplegend.png')
    #plt.show()
    plt.close()

from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import ImageGrid
import matplotlib.image as mpimg

img_list=[]
for f in os.listdir(htmldir):
    if ('seqclust' in f) and ('.png' in f):
        img_list.append(mpimg.imread(os.path.join(htmldir, f)))

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(22., 33.))
grid = ImageGrid(fig, 111,  # similar to subplot(111)
                 nrows_ncols=(1, 3),  # creates 2x3 grid of axes
                 axes_pad=0.1,  # pad between axes in inch.
                 share_all=True)  
grid[0].get_yaxis().set_ticks([])
grid[0].get_xaxis().set_ticks([])

for ax, im in zip(grid, img_list):
    # Iterating over the grid returns the Axes.
    ax.imshow(im)

plt.show()
